  "text": "Theorem 7 (Kenmotsu representation, [CITATION_1] ). Let Σ be a simply connected 2-dimensional smooth manifold and H : Σ → R be a non-zero C 1 −function. Let g : Σ → C ∪ {∞} be a smooth map satisfying (9) for H. Then there exists a branched immersion x : Σ → R 3 with Gauss map g and mean curvature H. Moreover, the immersion is unique up to similarity transformations of R 3 and it can be recovered using the equation",
